  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in serious criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Potential imprisonment up to 20 years\n- Significant fines (often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved)\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Criminal record\n\n2. Specific Statute Considerations:\n- 18 U.S. Code \u00a7 1956 covers federal money laundering offenses\n- Penalties can vary based on specific circumstances of the crime\n- Aggravating factors can increase potential sentencing\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nThese penalties can be complex and depend on specific case details. Actual sentencing would be determined by a federal judge considering multiple factors.\n\nWould you like me to provide more detailed information about money laundering laws?",
